                <div class="full-desc-about-cnt anim-elem">
                    <div class="centred-full-desc-a">
                        <p>There is no doubt that Europe continues to be a key destination for Foreign Direct Investment (FDI), accounting for 13 of the 25 countries in the A. T. Kearney&rsquo;s 2016 FDI Confidence Index. Last year Europe saw 5,083 FDI projects (up 14%) and 217,666 jobs (up 17%).</p>
<p>And there is no doubt that competition for prime assets and the best investment opportunities is likely to intensify due to globalization and the wealth being created in emerging economies.</p>
<p>At the moment investments in Western European countries represent great value for money. This is due to low EBITDA, high levels of corporate debt, the weakness of the Euro following the financial crisis and a regulatory environment that welcomes FDI.</p>
                    </div>
